President Barack Obama has proclaimed the week of December 1-7, 2013, as Minority Enterprise Development Week. In his proclamation, he emphasizes the importance of minority-owned businesses in driving progress in America's economy and society. These businesses employ nearly 6 million Americans and contribute $1 trillion to the economy each year. The president highlights the unique perspectives and advantages minority entrepreneurs bring to the international marketplace. He also mentions the efforts of his administration to empower minority entrepreneurs by connecting them with contracts and access to capital. The proclamation calls upon all Americans to celebrate and recognize the contributions of minority enterprises during this week.